    bio:"Renee Gentle is a Clinical Psychologist with over 15 years of experience in the assessment, diagnosis, and treatment of a wide range of psychological conditions. Throughout her career, Renee has worked across various clinical settings – including private practice and government agencies – providing her with a rich and diverse background in client care.\n\nRenee’s therapeutic approach is client-centred, focusing on building strong, supportive relationships and fostering an empathetic, non-judgemental environment. She employs evidence-based interventions to empower clients to actively participate in their mental health journey. Her goal is to help individuals develop the skills and strategies they need to overcome challenges, enhance wellbeing, and achieve long-term emotional balance.\n\nRenee has advanced her understanding of brain-body functioning through certification in neurofeedback, an advanced, non-invasive biofeedback technique that supports self-regulation and optimal brain performance.\n\nIn addition to her clinical work, Renee has an interest in the training and development of psychologists. She is a Board-Approved Supervisor and BCIA-accredited Neurofeedback Mentor, providing guidance and professional development to emerging practitioners within the field.\n\nRenee is a Member of the Australian Psychological Society (APS), a Fellow of the APS College of Clinical Psychologists, and a Member of the Applied Neuroscience Society of Australasia (ANSA).",
