    interests:["Depression", "Anxiety Disorders including social anxiety, phobias, panic attacks, general", "Stress and worry including adults with ADHD", "Pain management", "Eating disorders", "Anger management", "Stress management", "Grief and Loss", "Trauma", "Posttraumatic Stress Disorder", "Obsessive compulsive Disorder, Panic Disorder, Agoraphobia", "Children with a range of behavioural or emotional concerns including Autism Spectrum Disorder and ADHD/ADD", "WorkCover and other compensation claims, Workers Compensation", "Workplace performance and enhancements", "Personal growth including assertiveness, self-esteem, social skills"],
    bio:"“Skilled trauma-informed clinician whose approach is grounded in care supported by experience, research and compassion.”\n\nDr Elisabeth (Elisa) Wilson-Evered is a senior Clinical Psychologist with over 30 years of experience supporting people across hospital, community, private and organisational settings.\n\nShe works with adolescents, adults and older adults who may be experiencing anxiety, depression, trauma, grief, stress, relationship challenges or complex life transitions. Many of Elisa’s clients are thoughtful, capable individuals who have been carrying significant responsibility or distress for some time and are ready for deeper, sustainable change.\n\nElisa has particular expertise in trauma recovery, emotional regulation, attachment patterns, and rebuilding confidence after difficult or overwhelming life experiences. She provides specialised care for military personnel, veterans, first responders and their families, and has a deep respect for the unique psychological demands of service roles. She also values her work with older adults navigating health challenges, identity shifts and later-life transitions.\n\nHer approach is calm, compassionate and collaborative. Elisa integrates evidence-based therapies including EMDR and clinical hypnosis within a trauma-informed framework. Her work is informed not only by extensive clinical experience, but also by leadership and research in psychology, ensuring clients receive thoughtful, current and ethically grounded care.\n\nClients often describe Elisa as steady, insightful and deeply respectful of each person’s story. She believes meaningful change happens when people feel safe, understood and supported to move at their own pace.\n\nElisa offers face-to-face appointments in South-East Queensland and telehealth sessions Australia-wide.\n\n“Depth, steadiness and evidence-based care for complex life challenges.”",
