    bio:"Tiffany is a psychologist who brings a grounded, open-minded, and compassionate approach to therapy. She values creating a space where people feel genuinely seen,\nheard, and understood, and where they can slow things down, make sense of what’s been weighing on them, and feel supported to move forward in ways that feel right for them.\nTiffany has a Master’s degree in Professional Psychology, and is especially passionate about supporting adults and young people. She welcomes children aged 5 and up, a\ndolescents, and adults, and works with clients across different stages of life, taking a developmentally informed and individualised approach. Her background in special needs\nsupport work has given her a strong understanding of neurodiversity and individual differences, which continues to shape the way she works. She approaches therapy with\npatience, flexibility, and deep respect for each person’s unique way of experiencing the world.\n\nHer therapeutic style is gentle, curious, and strengths-based. While Tiffany draws on evidence-based approaches, she tailors therapy to the individual, recognising that no\ntwo people or journeys are the same. She aims to meet each client where they are, at their own pace.\n\nAt the heart of Tiffany’s work is a belief that everyone has strengths, even during times when they may feel hard to access. Therapy with Tiffany is a space to reflect,\nbuild understanding, and reconnect. Her hope is to support clients to feel grounded and empowered as they navigate life’s challenges.",
